## Digital Badges + Limited Edition Items

On top of the prize pool, we are giving out a rare Achievement Badge to every hacker that made it to the finish line (submitted a project):

![Badges](https://i.imgur.com/pAbnNcP.png)

You can find it on your Codédex User Profile (i.e., [@sonny](https://www.codedex.io/@sonn)) and via email from Accredible.

And if that's not enough, we added two new limited edition items to our [Merch Shop](https://www.codedex.io/shop): Summer Hackathon poster (signed) + Summer Hackathon beach towel! 🏖️

---


## And... that's a wrap!

From the bottom of my heart and the whole Codédex team, THANK YOU to all 259 teams (!) that submitted a project for our first-ever Summer Hackathon. There were so many beauuutiful projects that completely blew us away — every one of you is seriously impressive and deserves a big pat on the back. 

Shoutout to the judges ([Jack](https://www.linkedin.com/in/jack-ratner-1359b45a), [Cat](https://www.linkedin.com/in/zhoucatherine), [Wyatt](https://www.linkedin.com/in/wyattades), [Juan](https://www.linkedin.com/in/juanpflores94), [Emmy](https://www.linkedin.com/in/emmycao/overlay/photo), [Miracle](https://www.linkedin.com/in/miracleawonuga)) for volunteering their time and reviewing all the projects and to our sponsors ([Wix Studio](https://www.wix.com/studio), [.xyz](https://gen.xyz), [Jam](https://jam.dev), [Sip & Play](https://www.sipnplaynyc.com), [Wolfram](https://www.wolframalpha.com)) for bringing this to life with us. 

This was a huge milestone and we are beyond grateful to have you as part of our growing community. We also learned so much and aim to do it bigger and better next time~ ✨

Hope you all have a great rest of your summer! 🫶

